casebody.data:
[Rockingham,

June, 1889.] Coburn v. Storer. Same v. Same. Assumpsit and Trover. Tried by the court, who found the facts and assessed damages. The defendant excepted. A. G. Osgood and David Gross, for the defendant. Wig gin Bernal d, for the plaintiff. Carpenter, J.

The plaintiff’s right to judgment is not contested.

Exceptions overruled.

Blodgett, J., did not sit: the others concurred.
